track_notes:
Just past the quarry and small lake at start of Moel Siabod itself, I took a slight detour due to the path being flooded. 

Leading up to the summit I took a more direct route which involves light scrambling over rocks. The main path is slightly further beyond the route I took. An OS map clearly shows this.

A fairly easy ascent, as described by Tom M1EYP.

Over the foot bridge on the lake, then follow the track up through the woods and into the open. Continue following it until it runs out, then head upwards!

Total time (including ops): 5hr 5m. Maximum difficulty: Swiss Alpine Club Grade T3 / Grade 1 Scramble. Uncurated GPX which may contain navigation errors, detours and hazards. Additional route information may be available at www.m1hax.uk. Track data by Richard M1HAX licensed under Creative Commons BY-NC-SA.
track_title: Moel Siabod Circuit from Northeast. Aug 2020.
